.\" Man page for btrfs-backup-ng snapshot
.TH BTRFS-BACKUP-NG-SNAPSHOT 1 "January 2026" "btrfs-backup-ng" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
btrfs-backup-ng-snapshot \- create snapshots only
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B btrfs-backup-ng snapshot
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Create snapshots of configured volumes without transferring to targets.
Useful for frequent local snapshots between less frequent remote backups.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dry-run
Show what would be done without making any changes.
.TP
.BI \-\-volume " PATH"
Only snapshot the specified volume(s). Can be specified multiple times.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Create snapshots for all configured volumes:
.B btrfs-backup-ng snapshot
.TP
Create snapshot for specific volume only:
.B btrfs-backup-ng snapshot --volume /home
.TP
Dry run:
.B btrfs-backup-ng snapshot --dry-run
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR btrfs-backup-ng (1),
